! Broadcast mode

Controls how SSE events for ''per-tab view-state tiddlers'' (`$:/StoryList`, `$:/HistoryList`, `$:/state/*` by default) propagate between connected browser tabs. MCP-tool changes and filesystem-watcher edits always broadcast to all tabs, regardless of mode.

|! |!Mode |!Description |
|<$radio tiddler="$:/config/wikilabs/tw-mcp/mode" value="default" default="default"/> |''Default'' |Per-tab view state stays per-tab. Browser-originated `$:/StoryList` changes do not cross-sync. |
|<$radio tiddler="$:/config/wikilabs/tw-mcp/mode" value="presentation"/> |''Presentation'' |One tab is the //presenter// and its view-state changes broadcast to all other tabs. Last-claim-wins. |
|<$radio tiddler="$:/config/wikilabs/tw-mcp/mode" value="main"/> |''Main'' |Like presentation, but a tab can claim the //i-am-main// admin role and gate who is allowed to present. ''Not yet wired in this version.'' |

